<title>USA: EU'S De Silguy sees euro as stable as German mark.</title>
<headline>EU'S De Silguy sees euro as stable as German mark.</headline>
<dateline>WASHINGTON 1997-04-29</dateline>
<text>
<p>European Union Commissioner of Monetary Affairs Yves Thibault de Silguy said Tuesday that he expected the euro to be as stable as the German mark.</p>
<p>&quot;It will be as stable as the German mark currently is,&quot; de Silguy said in a speech to the Institute of International Finance.</p>
<p>European Union member states that qualify for the first wave of monetary union are scheduled to launch the euro in January 1999.</p>
